{
  "text": "Infrared imaging inspection is well known as a noncontact measurement technique where the inspection can be done without interrupting or shutting down the operation of a system. It offers many advantages over conventional temperature measurement technique, including the capability of fast response times, wide temperature ranges, two-dimensional data acquisition, high spatial resolution, safe, reliable and very cost-effective approach for an electrical power system maintenance program [CITATION_1] .",
